import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
data=pd.read_csv("C:\\Users\\ASUS\\Downloads\\WEEK3 new\\WEEK3\\Immigration\\visa.csv")

count_positive = 0
count_negative = 0
count_neutral = 0

for sentiment in data['sentiment']:
    if sentiment == 'Positive':
        count_positive += 1
    else:
        count_negative += 1
total=len(data)
positive_response= (count_positive / total) * 100
negative_response = (count_negative / total) * 100
myexplode = [0.2, 0]
y=[positive_response,negative_response]
plt.pie(y,labels=[str(round(positive_response,2))+"%",str(round(negative_response,2))+"%"],explode = myexplode, shadow = True,colors=["g","r"])
plt.title("Check IN tweet % distribution")
plt.legend(["positive","negative"])
plt.show()

LDA for positive tweets¶

In [4]:
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import CountVectorizer
from sklearn.decomposition import LatentDirichletAllocation

from sklearn.feature_extraction import text

# Read the positive reviews data
positive_reviews = pd.read_csv("C:\\Users\\ASUS\\Downloads\\WEEK3 new\\WEEK3\\Immigration\\visa - Copy.csv")

# Combine reviews into a list
reviews = positive_reviews['tweet'].tolist()

# Create a custom stop words list if needed
custom_stop_words = ["read", "good", "disney", "yorker", "day", "didn", "stay", "great", "check", "booked", "like", "die", "told", "friendly", "clean", "sehr", "das", "zimmer", "und", "nice", "did", "was", "really", "safe", "walk", "close", "got"]

# Extend the default English stop words list with custom stop words
stop_words = list(text.ENGLISH_STOP_WORDS) + custom_stop_words

# Vectorize the text data
vectorizer = CountVectorizer(max_df=0.95, min_df=2, stop_words=stop_words)
X = vectorizer.fit_transform(reviews)

# Apply LDA for topic modeling
num_topics = 5
lda = LatentDirichletAllocation(n_components=num_topics, random_state=42)
lda.fit(X)

# Extract top words for each topic
feature_names = vectorizer.get_feature_names_out()
topics = []
for topic_idx, topic in enumerate(lda.components_):
    top_words_idx = topic.argsort()[-10:]
    top_words = [feature_names[i] for i in top_words_idx]
    topics.append(top_words)

# Print the top words for each topic (possible reasons for positive reviews)
for i, topic in enumerate(topics):
    print(f"Topic {i + 1}: {', '.join(topic)}")

Topic 1: arrival, lounge, access, entry, staff, credit, know, days, ur, visa
Topic 2: come, officer, sure, access, lounge, need, card, year, free, visa
Topic 3: urgent, country, flight, business, arrange, kindly, dear, germany, going, visa
Topic 4: days, minister, amp, visas, arrival, valid, sir, immigration, visa, flights
Topic 5: immigration, urgent, respected, customs, board, flight, new, stuck, visa, help

Observation on positive tweet¶

  • ### The lounge employees are friendly and well-informed.
  • ### They can respond to queries on entry, exit, and visa prerequisites.
  • ### Moreover, they can assist customers with credit card problems.

Recommendations:¶

  • ### Train the lounge staff on the most recent entry and visa regulations for every nation.
  • ### Consider of providing lounge visitors with a complimentary visa assistance service.

Word Cloud for positive tweets¶

In [5]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from wordcloud import WordCloud

# Create a word cloud object
wc = WordCloud(background_color="white", max_font_size=50)

# Check the type of the topics variable
if isinstance(topics, list):
    # Convert the topics variable to a list of strings
    topics = [" ".join(topic) for topic in topics]

# Generate the word cloud
wc.generate(" ".join(topics))

# Plot the word cloud
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
plt.imshow(wc)
plt.axis("off")
plt.title("Top Words in Positive Reviews")
plt.show()

LDA for Negative tweets¶

In [6]:
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import CountVectorizer
from sklearn.decomposition import LatentDirichletAllocation
from sklearn.feature_extraction import text

# Read the negative reviews data
negative_reviews = pd.read_csv("C:\\Users\\ASUS\\Downloads\\WEEK3 new\\WEEK3\\Immigration\\visa - Copy (2).csv")

# Combine reviews into a list
reviews = negative_reviews['tweet'].tolist()

# Create a custom stop words list if needed
custom_stop_words = ["read", "good", "disney", "yorker", "day", "didn", "stay", "great", "check", "booked", "like", "die", "told", "friendly", "clean", "sehr", "das", "zimmer", "und", "nice", "did", "was", "really", "safe", "walk", "close", "got"]

# Convert the custom stop words to a list
custom_stop_words = list(custom_stop_words)

# Extend the default English stop words list with custom stop words
stop_words = list(text.ENGLISH_STOP_WORDS) + custom_stop_words

# Vectorize the text data
vectorizer = CountVectorizer(max_df=0.95, min_df=2, stop_words=stop_words)
X = vectorizer.fit_transform(reviews)

# Apply LDA for topic modeling
num_topics = 5
lda = LatentDirichletAllocation(n_components=num_topics, random_state=42)
lda.fit(X)

# Extract top words for each topic
feature_names = vectorizer.get_feature_names_out()
topics = []
for topic_idx, topic in enumerate(lda.components_):
    top_words_idx = topic.argsort()[-10:]
    top_words = [feature_names[i] for i in top_words_idx]
    topics.append(top_words)

# Print the top words for each topic (possible reasons for negative reviews)
for i, topic in enumerate(topics):
    print(f"Topic {i + 1}: {', '.join(topic)}")

Topic 1: absolutely, board, allow, india, flight, hours, officer, refused, immigration, visa
Topic 2: card, experience, today, board, lounge, flight, reason, india, denied, visa
Topic 3: worst, website, man, claim, signature, denied, access, lounge, card, visa
Topic 4: hours, went, valid, asked, visas, flights, experience, need, visa, staff
Topic 5: hours, refused, flights, immigration, went, visas, need, india, visa, stuck

Observation on negative tweet¶

  • ### In Bangalore's airport cafés, customers dislike hot coffee.
  • ### Some feel the coffee is overpriced.
  • ### People claim the coffee is not very good.
  • ### Customers believe the service is sluggish and ineffective.
  • ### People find the cafes are unclean and unsanitary.

Recommendations:¶

  • ### The immigration office and airport lounges should assess their protocols and instruct their employees on the value of providing excellent customer service and protecting customers' rights.
  • ### The immigration office needs to put in place a mechanism that gives travelers with connecting flights priority when processing visas and must increase the number of employees on duty during peak hours.
  • ### Passengers should be given clear and straightforward information by the immigration office on the visa application procedure and the reason for the visa's rejection.
  • ### Passengers who were denied visas should receive assistance from the immigration office.
